**The most critical finding (Issues #1-3):** Working directory isolation — the headline feature of Story 4-2 — is **structurally incomplete**. The scoped tools infrastructure exists in `scoped.py`, `spawn.py`, and `roles.py`, but the orchestrator pipeline has no mechanism to receive or propagate `target_dir`. During a rebuild, all agent tool calls and all bash commands (tests, CI, git) will operate on Shipyard's own source tree, not the target project. This needs `OrchestratorState` to carry `working_dir`, all agent nodes to thread it to `run_sub_agent()`, and `_run_bash()` to accept a `cwd` parameter.

